# 真遇圈 Architecture Guide

## Layer Structure

```
App Layer (UI)
├── Screens (Full-page views)
├── Widgets (Reusable components)
├── Navigation (Bottom nav, routing)
└── Theme (Colors, styles)

Business Logic Layer
├── Services (Business logic)
├── Models (Data structures)
└── State Management (setState)

Data Layer
├── SharedPreferences (Local storage)
└── Mock Data (Development)
```

## File Organization

### Core Files
- `lib/main.dart` - App entry point, initialization, theme config
- `lib/app.dart` - MaterialApp configuration, navigation structure

### Models (`lib/models/`)
- `user_model.dart` - User profile data
- `camp_model.dart` - Camp plan and trip data
- `gear_model.dart` - Gear items and equipment
- `wiki_model.dart` - Wiki articles and steps
- `post_model.dart` - Discovery feed posts
- `log_model.dart` - Camp log entries
- `message_model.dart` - Community chat messages

### Services (`lib/services/`)
- `local_storage_service.dart` - SharedPreferences wrapper
- `data_service.dart` - Mock data provider

### Screens (`lib/screens/`)
- `discovery_screen.dart` - Tab 1: Feed, Wiki, Search
- `plan_screen.dart` - Tab 2: Plans, Gear checklist
- `camp_log_screen.dart` - Tab 3: Timeline journal
- `community_screen.dart` - Tab 4: AI chat, Circles
- `profile_screen.dart` - Tab 5: User profile, Stats
- `creator_profile_screen.dart` - Creator detail view
- `wiki_detail_screen.dart` - Wiki article detail
- `post_detail_screen.dart` - Feed post detail

### Widgets (`lib/widgets/`)
- `custom_bottom_nav.dart` - Bottom navigation bar
- `custom_app_bar.dart` - Custom app bars
- `gear_card.dart` - Gear item card
- `wiki_card.dart` - Wiki article card
- `plan_card.dart` - Plan summary card
- `post_card.dart` - Discovery feed card
- `message_bubble.dart` - Chat message bubble
- `log_entry_card.dart` - Timeline log entry

### Utils (`lib/utils/`)
- `constants.dart` - App constants, colors, sizes
- `theme.dart` - ThemeData definition
- `extensions.dart` - Dart extensions

## State Management Rules
- Use `StatefulWidget` with `setState()` for local state
- Pass data down through constructors
- Use callbacks to bubble events up
- Keep state close to where it's used
- Avoid global state when possible

## Data Flow
1. Services fetch/manage data
2. Screens hold state and business logic
3. Widgets receive data via props
4. User actions trigger callbacks
5. Callbacks update state via setState()
6. UI rebuilds reactively
